step.context:
\text{The following substitution would convert}\\
\sin  x\cdot\sin 2x\cdot\sin 3x\text{ to the more easily}\\
\text{integrable sum of sine or cosine form}

step.tex:

\begin{align}
  I &= \int \dfrac{1}{4} [ \sin 2 x - \sin 6x +sin 4x] dx \\
    &=\dfrac{1}{4}\left[\int \sin 2x dx - \int \sin 6x dx 
      +\int \sin 4x dx \right] \\
    &=  \dfrac {1} {4}\left[\cos 2 x + \cos6 x -\cos 4x\right]+C
\end{align}
